            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>This Week's Snapshot: Creative Thresholds Are Rising</h2>
<p>Multiple TikTok Shop overseas teams reported significant changes in creative review feedback for new product cold launches this week—<strong>pass rates for non-original content dropped, and traffic support for repurposed creatives has visibly shrunk</strong>. Additionally, top-performing creatives from last week are decaying roughly 20-30% faster, rendering the "copy-the-winner" cold launch strategy increasingly ineffective.</p>
<p>These three converging signals mean cold launch creative strategies need systematic upgrades. This week, Yiyu Media assisted several clients in restructuring their creative pools—here are our key observations.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Shift 1: Repurposed Content Pass Rates Declining</h2>
<p>The most frequently reported issue this week: lightly edited creatives that previously passed review consistently are now being batch-rejected.</p>
<p><strong>Probable cause</strong>: The platform is improving detection precision for "low-originality content," especially composite edits with music replacements.</p>
<p><strong>Impact</strong>: Teams relying on repurposing to quickly test creatives are seeing notable spend fluctuations, with some accounts experiencing wasted impressions due to delayed creative replacements.</p>
<p><strong>Recommendations</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Prioritize adding real-person or in-house filmed content—aim for 40%+ of your creative pool</li>
<li>Light edits need more original elements: unique caption styles, voiceovers, product usage scenarios</li>
<li>Establish a pre-review workflow to check originality before submission</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Shift 2: Viral Creative Lifecycles Shortening</h2>
<p>Creatives that generated steady orders last week are seeing widespread conversion rate declines this week. One home goods出海 team reported their main "unboxing + usage demo" creative dropped from 2.8% CVR last week to 1.9% this week.</p>
<p><strong>Probable cause</strong>: Platform traffic distribution is dynamically adjusting—once a creative's exposure threshold is reached, algorithmic weighting decreases; user fatigue with similar content is also accumulating.</p>
<p><strong>Impact</strong>: Single-product dependency on one creative set increases risk. Cold launch windows are shrinking, requiring faster creative iteration cycles.</p>
<p><strong>Recommendations</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>During cold launch, prepare <strong>3-5 differentiated creatives</strong> instead of 1-2 to test repeatedly</li>
<li>Build creative AB frameworks: prepare both "impact" direction (high-tempo, high-stimulation) and "nurture" direction (slow-narrative, trust-building) for the same product</li>
<li>Set creative decay alerts—trigger replacement when a creative's CTR drops 15%+ for 3 consecutive days</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Shift 3: Multi-Account Creative Diversification</h2>
<p>Another trend observed this week: <strong>brand accounts with high creative overlap across accounts are seeing lower overall spend compared to diversified account groups</strong>. </p>
<p><strong>Probable cause</strong>: Platform algorithms are identifying "matrix-style manipulation" behavior, and similar creatives across multiple accounts are flagged as low-quality signals.</p>
<p><strong>Impact</strong>: Batch-copying creatives across accounts is becoming less efficient. More localization is needed at the creative level.</p>
<p><strong>Recommendations</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Multi-account creative diversification means more than swapping captions or voiceovers—it requires differentiation in <strong>scenarios, actors, and linguistic style</strong></li>
<li>For the same product, prepare at least 3 creative versions targeting: young female personas, homemaker personas, and high-spending power personas</li>
<li>Tag creative versions carefully to avoid same-version creatives being mistakenly delivered to the same account group</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Week-in-Review Summary</h2>
<p>This week's TikTok Shop cold launch shifts all point to one conclusion: <strong>the weight of creative quality and differentiation is rising, and quantity-driven approaches are losing effectiveness</strong>. For overseas teams, rather than debating "which platform is better," it's more valuable to build a solid creative pool foundation first.</p>
<p>If you're experiencing specific creative review or spend issues this week, feel free to reach out. Yiyu Media has assisted multiple teams with creative pool diagnostics and restructuring—we have hands-on data to share.</p>
